     Feb. 14 (Bloomberg) --Lone Pine Capital LLC slashed its
stake in  News Corp. (NWSA) , the media company being investigated by
U.K. authorities for hacking phones of celebrities and
politicians.  The hedge fund run by Stephen Mandel Jr. decreased its
holdings in New York-based News Corp. by 93 percent to 1.91
million shares, according to a regulatory filing today by the
Greenwich, Connecticut-based firm as of Dec. 31. News Corp. is
run by Chairman and Chief Executive Officer  Rupert Murdoch , 80.
The firm acquired 6.24 million shares in  FMC Technologies Inc. (FTI) ,
a Houston-based maker of oil field equipment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Clark in New York at 
